	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65024565"><p>It's the problem when you have positions in government that are given a goal of reducing X by Y every year without a end point (or worse the ever favorite 'project 0' initiatives).  The goals need to be set to get to a certain point of diminishing returns and then the positions eliminated and tax dollars shifted to something else.  Instead, government only grows and never shrinks.  Keeping obsolete agencies and projects alive forever.</p></div>
	</div>

