	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65024597"><p>Wikipedia has a nice table of vehicle fatality statistics. Deaths per mile decreased steadily from roughly 1966 through 2014. In 2014, there were 1.08 deaths per million miles traveled. Since then, deaths/mile have <b> <i>increased</i> </b> by around 25%.

</p><p>Is it possible that new safety regulations are becoming counterproductive? Just as an example: FMVSS 214 and 226 started a phased program in 2013 that has led to airbags in the pillars, and thick pillars reduce visibility.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65024597">

